searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"BenchGecko","doc":"The CoinGecko for AI.\n\nBenchGecko provides structured access to AI model benchmarks, pricing data,\nand agent comparison. Query 300+ models across 50+ providers with real\nbenchmark scores, latency metrics, and transparent pricing.","ref":"BenchGecko.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Quick Start - BenchGecko","doc":"model = BenchGecko.get_model(\"gpt-4o\")\n    model.name       #=> \"GPT-4o\"\n    model.provider   #=> \"OpenAI\"\n\n    BenchGecko.score(model, \"MMLU\")  #=> 88.7","ref":"BenchGecko.html#module-quick-start"},{"type":"module","title":"Comparing Models - BenchGecko","doc":"BenchGecko.compare_models(\"gpt-4o\", \"claude-3.5-sonnet\")\n    |> Map.get(:benchmark_diff)\n    |> Enum.each(fn {bench, diff} -> IO.puts(\"#{bench}: #{diff}\") end)\n\nFull documentation at [benchgecko.ai](https://benchgecko.ai).","ref":"BenchGecko.html#module-comparing-models"},{"type":"function","title":"BenchGecko.benchmark_categories/0","doc":"List all benchmark categories tracked by BenchGecko.","ref":"BenchGecko.html#benchmark_categories/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - BenchGecko.benchmark_categories/0","doc":"BenchGecko.benchmark_categories()\n    |> Enum.each(fn {key, info} ->\n      IO.puts(\"#{info.name}: #{Enum.join(info.benchmarks, \", \")}\")\n    end)","ref":"BenchGecko.html#benchmark_categories/0-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"BenchGecko.cheapest_above/2","doc":"Find the cheapest model that meets a minimum score on a benchmark.","ref":"BenchGecko.html#cheapest_above/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - BenchGecko.cheapest_above/2","doc":"model = BenchGecko.cheapest_above(\"MMLU\", 85.0)\n    IO.puts(\"#{model.name} at $#{BenchGecko.cost_per_million(model)}/M tokens\")","ref":"BenchGecko.html#cheapest_above/2-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"BenchGecko.compare_models/2","doc":"Compare two models side by side across benchmarks and pricing.\n\nReturns a map with `:model_a`, `:model_b`, `:benchmark_diff`, `:cheaper`,\nand `:cost_ratio`. Positive diff values mean model A scores higher.","ref":"BenchGecko.html#compare_models/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - BenchGecko.compare_models/2","doc":"result = BenchGecko.compare_models(\"gpt-4o\", \"claude-3.5-sonnet\")\n    result.cheaper\n    #=> \"gpt-4o\"\n\n    result.benchmark_diff\n    |> Enum.filter(fn {_k, v} -> v != nil end)\n    |> Enum.each(fn {bench, diff} ->\n      IO.puts(\"#{bench}: #{diff}\")\n    end)","ref":"BenchGecko.html#compare_models/2-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"BenchGecko.cost_per_million/1","doc":"Calculate cost per million tokens (average of input and output).","ref":"BenchGecko.html#cost_per_million/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - BenchGecko.cost_per_million/1","doc":"model = BenchGecko.get_model!(\"gpt-4o\")\n    BenchGecko.cost_per_million(model)\n    #=> 6.25","ref":"BenchGecko.html#cost_per_million/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"BenchGecko.estimate_cost/3","doc":"Estimate inference cost for a given token volume.","ref":"BenchGecko.html#estimate_cost/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - BenchGecko.estimate_cost/3","doc":"BenchGecko.estimate_cost(\"gpt-4o\", 1_000_000, 500_000)\n    #=> %{model: \"GPT-4o\", input_cost: 2.5, output_cost: 5.0, total: 7.5}","ref":"BenchGecko.html#estimate_cost/3-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"BenchGecko.get_model/1","doc":"Retrieve a model by its identifier.\n\nReturns `{:ok, model}` if found, `:error` otherwise.","ref":"BenchGecko.html#get_model/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - BenchGecko.get_model/1","doc":"{:ok, model} = BenchGecko.get_model(\"gpt-4o\")\n    model.name\n    #=> \"GPT-4o\"","ref":"BenchGecko.html#get_model/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"BenchGecko.get_model!/1","doc":"Retrieve a model, raising if not found.","ref":"BenchGecko.html#get_model!/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - BenchGecko.get_model!/1","doc":"model = BenchGecko.get_model!(\"claude-3.5-sonnet\")\n    model.provider\n    #=> \"Anthropic\"","ref":"BenchGecko.html#get_model!/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"BenchGecko.list_models/0","doc":"List all available model identifiers.","ref":"BenchGecko.html#list_models/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - BenchGecko.list_models/0","doc":"BenchGecko.list_models()\n    #=> [\"claude-3.5-sonnet\", \"deepseek-v3\", \"gemini-2.0-flash\", ...]","ref":"BenchGecko.html#list_models/0-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"BenchGecko.score/2","doc":"Get the score for a specific benchmark on a model.","ref":"BenchGecko.html#score/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - BenchGecko.score/2","doc":"model = BenchGecko.get_model!(\"gpt-4o\")\n    BenchGecko.score(model, \"MMLU\")\n    #=> 88.7","ref":"BenchGecko.html#score/2-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"BenchGecko.top_models/2","doc":"Find models scoring above a threshold on a given benchmark.\n\nResults are sorted by score descending.","ref":"BenchGecko.html#top_models/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - BenchGecko.top_models/2","doc":"BenchGecko.top_models(\"MMLU\", 87.0)\n    |> Enum.each(fn m -> IO.puts(\"#{m.name}: #{BenchGecko.score(m, \"MMLU\")}\") end)","ref":"BenchGecko.html#top_models/2-examples"},{"type":"module","title":"BenchGecko.Agent","doc":"Represents an AI agent with capabilities and evaluation scores.","ref":"BenchGecko.Agent.html"},{"type":"type","title":"BenchGecko.Agent.t/0","doc":"","ref":"BenchGecko.Agent.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"module","title":"BenchGecko.Model","doc":"Represents an AI model with benchmark scores, pricing, and metadata.","ref":"BenchGecko.Model.html"},{"type":"type","title":"BenchGecko.Model.t/0","doc":"","ref":"BenchGecko.Model.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"extras","title":"BenchGecko for Elixir","doc":"# BenchGecko for Elixir\n\n**The CoinGecko for AI.** Elixir client for accessing AI model benchmarks, comparing language models, estimating inference costs, and discovering AI agents.\n\nBenchGecko tracks 300+ AI models across 50+ providers with real benchmark scores, latency metrics, and transparent pricing. This package gives you structured access to that data in idiomatic Elixir with pattern matching, pipes, and typespecs throughout.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Installation - BenchGecko for Elixir","doc":"Add `benchgecko` to your list of dependencies in `mix.exs`:\n\n```elixir\ndef deps do\n  [\n    {:benchgecko, \"~> 0.1.0\"}\n  ]\nend\n```\n\nThen run `mix deps.get`.","ref":"readme.html#installation"},{"type":"extras","title":"Quick Start - BenchGecko for Elixir","doc":"```elixir\n# Look up any model\n{:ok, model} = BenchGecko.get_model(\"claude-3.5-sonnet\")\nmodel.name       #=> \"Claude 3.5 Sonnet\"\nmodel.provider   #=> \"Anthropic\"\n\nBenchGecko.score(model, \"MMLU\")  #=> 88.7\n\n# Bang variant raises on unknown models\nmodel = BenchGecko.get_model!(\"gpt-4o\")\n```","ref":"readme.html#quick-start"},{"type":"extras","title":"Comparing Models - BenchGecko for Elixir","doc":"The comparison engine uses Elixir maps to surface benchmark differences and pricing ratios. Positive diff values mean the first model scores higher:\n\n```elixir\n\"gpt-4o\"\n|> BenchGecko.compare_models(\"claude-3.5-sonnet\")\n|> then(fn result ->\n  IO.puts(\"Cheaper: #{result.cheaper}\")\n  IO.puts(\"Cost ratio: #{result.cost_ratio}\")\n\n  result.benchmark_diff\n  |> Enum.filter(fn {_bench, diff} -> diff != nil end)\n  |> Enum.each(fn {bench, diff} ->\n    winner = if diff >= 0, do: \"GPT-4o\", else: \"Claude 3.5 Sonnet\"\n    IO.puts(\"#{bench}: #{winner} by #{abs(diff)} pts\")\n  end)\nend)\n```","ref":"readme.html#comparing-models"},{"type":"extras","title":"Cost Estimation - BenchGecko for Elixir","doc":"Estimate inference costs before committing to a provider. All prices are per million tokens:\n\n```elixir\ncase BenchGecko.estimate_cost(\"gpt-4o\", 2_000_000, 500_000) do\n  %{total: total, input_cost: input, output_cost: output} ->\n    IO.puts(\"Input: $#{input}, Output: $#{output}, Total: $#{total}\")\n\n  :error ->\n    IO.puts(\"Model not found or missing pricing data\")\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#cost-estimation"},{"type":"extras","title":"Finding the Right Model - BenchGecko for Elixir","doc":"Filter models by benchmark performance with pipes and pattern matching:\n\n```elixir\n# All models scoring 87+ on MMLU, sorted by score\nBenchGecko.top_models(\"MMLU\", 87.0)\n|> Enum.each(fn model ->\n  IO.puts(\"#{model.name}: #{BenchGecko.score(model, \"MMLU\")}\")\nend)\n\n# Cheapest model above a quality threshold\ncase BenchGecko.cheapest_above(\"MMLU\", 85.0) do\n  nil -> IO.puts(\"No model meets the threshold\")\n  model -> IO.puts(\"#{model.name} at $#{BenchGecko.cost_per_million(model)}/M tokens\")\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#finding-the-right-model"},{"type":"extras","title":"Benchmark Categories - BenchGecko for Elixir","doc":"BenchGecko organizes 40+ benchmarks into categories covering reasoning, coding, math, instruction following, safety, multimodal, multilingual, and long context evaluation:\n\n```elixir\nBenchGecko.benchmark_categories()\n|> Enum.each(fn {_key, info} ->\n  IO.puts(\"#{info.name}: #{Enum.join(info.benchmarks, \", \")}\")\n  IO.puts(\"  #{info.description}\")\nend)\n```","ref":"readme.html#benchmark-categories"},{"type":"extras","title":"Built-in Model Catalog - BenchGecko for Elixir","doc":"The package ships with a curated catalog of major models from OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Meta, Mistral, and DeepSeek. Each entry includes benchmark scores, parameter counts, context window sizes, and per-token pricing.\n\nAll data is compiled into the module at build time for zero-overhead lookups -- no HTTP calls, no external dependencies.\n\n```elixir\nmodel = BenchGecko.get_model!(\"deepseek-v3\")\nmodel.parameters       #=> 671\nmodel.context_window   #=> 128_000\nBenchGecko.cost_per_million(model)  #=> 0.685\n```","ref":"readme.html#built-in-model-catalog"},{"type":"extras","title":"Typespecs and Documentation - BenchGecko for Elixir","doc":"Every public function has `@spec` and `@doc` annotations. Generate local documentation with:\n\n```bash\nmix docs\n```","ref":"readme.html#typespecs-and-documentation"},{"type":"extras","title":"Resources - BenchGecko for Elixir","doc":"- [BenchGecko](https://benchgecko.ai) -- Full platform with interactive comparisons\n- [Source Code](https://github.com/BenchGecko/benchgecko-elixir) -- Contributions welcome","ref":"readme.html#resources"},{"type":"extras","title":"License - BenchGecko for Elixir","doc":"MIT License. See [LICENSE](LICENSE) for details.","ref":"readme.html#license"},{"type":"extras","title":"LICENSE","doc":"MIT License\n\nCopyright (c) 2026 BenchGecko\n\nPermission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy\nof this software and associated documentation files (the \"Software\"), to deal\nin the Software without restriction, including without limitation the rights\nto use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell\ncopies of the Software, and to permit persons to whom the Software is\nfurnished to do so, subject to the following conditions:\n\nThe above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in all\ncopies or substantial portions of the Software.\n\nTHE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED \"AS IS\", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR\nIMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,\nFITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE\nAUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER\nLIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM,\nOUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE\nSOFTWARE.","ref":"license.html"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.1"}}